VEVENT.LOCATION: Mount Waverley Youth Centre - Meeting Room 1
VEVENT.DESCRIPTION:
Celebrate the end of exams with our classic end of exams party - now bigger and better!

This time\, we've collaborated with a big range of special interest clubs to provide you the perfect send-off for your exams\, to play as many video/board/card games as you can\, mingle with fellow nerds\, and relieve your post-exam stress!

We will be hosting our biggest EXP yet on Friday the 22nd of November at the Mount Waverley Youth Centre.
This year\, food and non-alcoholic beverages will provided as part of your ticket cost! And\, alcoholic drinks will be available for purchase at student prices.

We would like to see as many of your happy selves at the event as possible so the event is open to everyone\, even if you are not an active member of one of the clubs.

The doors will open at 6pm at the venue which is conveniently located right next to Mount Waverley train station (and the 733 and 623 bus lines)

Tickets are now open\, and will close on Wednesday the 20th of  November. Get them ASAP to secure your spot!
Tickets pricing are as follows:
$15 with MSA membership
$20 without MSA membership
(please bring your student ID card as MSA membership will be checked at the door)

Link to tickets --> https://www.eventbrite.com.au/e/exp-6-revenge-of-the-sixth-tickets-77250952679
---------------------------------------------------------------------
If you have any access needs or queries\, please advise us at: 
cardcollective@monashclubs.org

or refer to the Senior Event Manager
Maiher Chopra
mscho12@student.monash.edu

We wish to acknowledge the people of the Kulin Nations - the Wurundjeri people\, on whose land we gather. We pay our respects to their Elders\, past and present.

***This is strictly an 18+ event. Please bring a current and valid photo ID. The venue and our clubs reserve the right to refuse entry. Our clubs encourage the responsible consumption of alcohol.***
